From Chris BeHanna Subject Re Carb Cleaners Do they work Performance Carb rebuild In article Dan Day writes In article Doug Schaffer writes How hard is a carb rebuild for moderately experienced backyard mechanic I've done my clutch and miscellaneous little engine The hardest part is usually getting the darned thing off the intake Rebuilding a carb is fun if you're into things with lots of little I used to rebuild them for all my friends' cars in high school so it doesn't take a Buy a carb rebuilding kit from an auto supply Buy a gallon of the best carb cleaning solvent you can find do they still make Tyme as a rule of thumb buy the one with the scariest warning Put it into a metal Make yourself a dipping can by punching holes in the bottom of a coffee can and attaching a wire handle to If the carb cleaner doesn't strip the paint right off the coffee can you're not using the right Use the can to soak the little stuff and just hang the big parts from a coat Wash them off with a garden hose wipe off excess water with paper towels and air Then remember where all the little parts Follow the rebuild kit's instructions concerning float height choke tension Bolt it back on the engine and admire the super clean carb on the filthy Heed this man's warnings If you get carb cleaner this strong on your hands your hands will be eaten Not Hence the dipping can Later Chris BeHanna DoD H D FXWG Wide Glide Jubilee's Red Lady Baby Bike Disclaimer Now why would NEC ZX needs a name agree with any of this anyway I was raised by a pack of wild corn